The paper discusses a framework for developing interactive visualizations that can scale to use back-end services as needed. This involves managing communication and state across different layers of the application, including UI events, server APIs, and database queries. The paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including human-computer interaction (HCI), databases (DB), distributed computing (DC), software engineering (SE), and programming languages (PL).
